 Edith Wharton articulated their political thought in response to the liberalism that reigned in Boston and, more specifically, at Harvard University, this book shows how each of these authors interrogated that liberalism's arguments for education, democracy and the political duties of the cultivated elite. Coit shows that the works of these authors contributed to a realist critique of a liberal New England idealism that fed into the narrative about 'the genteel tradition', which shaped the study of US literature during the twentieth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh1 aBoggs, Colleen Glenney, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoyle, Laura, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFumagalli, Maria Cristina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z97831107804060 cprintz978147447540240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978147447542640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474475426423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474475426/original  a978-3-11-078040-6  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022